WEBVTT

00:04.214 --> 00:07.218
Sh. I'm not supposed to be in the attic.

00:07.305 --> 00:09.271
Mom and Dad said it's off limits.

00:11.109 --> 00:12.804
And no kids allowed

00:12.829 --> 00:15.211
means it's the perfect place
to try my new invention.

00:15.247 --> 00:17.380
A virtual reality helmet!

00:17.416 --> 00:20.150
And I do not need
my siblings knowing about it,

00:20.185 --> 00:23.319
because with them around,
nothing lasts long.

00:24.903 --> 00:27.323
I had that pogo stick for three weeks.

00:27.359 --> 00:29.325
Video game, two days.

00:31.129 --> 00:32.395
Dead on arrival.

00:32.430 --> 00:34.431
This helmet may not look like much,

00:34.466 --> 00:36.266
but when I put it on...

00:38.303 --> 00:40.103
there's nowhere I can't go.

00:42.274 --> 00:44.174
Precision is everything.

00:47.312 --> 00:49.279
One false move, and my next trip

00:49.314 --> 00:51.314
will be to a virtual hospital.

00:53.452 --> 00:55.351
Who's up here?

00:55.387 --> 00:57.187
What are you doing?

01:01.526 --> 01:03.293
Uh, playing a new game called

01:03.328 --> 01:05.328
take big steps and knock things down.

01:05.363 --> 01:08.064
That's not new. We've been
playing it for years.

01:08.100 --> 01:09.265
You know you're not
supposed to be up here.

01:09.301 --> 01:12.068
- Neither are you.
- We heard noises.

01:12.104 --> 01:13.403
We thought the house had rats.

01:13.438 --> 01:15.238
To be honest, I'm
disappointed it doesn't.

01:15.273 --> 01:18.274
If you want rats,
you know where you should play?

01:18.310 --> 01:20.110
The old skunk den under the house.

01:25.150 --> 01:26.516
Lewie and Beast's baby book.

01:26.551 --> 01:29.185
Why is our baby book a shoebox?

01:29.221 --> 01:30.353
Mom and Dad were pretty burned out

01:30.388 --> 01:32.255
by the time you guys came along.

01:32.290 --> 01:34.057
Be glad you have a shoebox.

01:34.092 --> 01:35.425
All Daphne has is
a sticky note that says

01:35.460 --> 01:37.360
"take pictures of Daphne."

01:37.395 --> 01:40.130
Cool. Our birth certificates.

01:40.165 --> 01:42.532
Check it. I was born at 11:58 p.m.

01:42.567 --> 01:45.502
I was born at 12:03 a.m.

01:45.537 --> 01:47.537
Mom and Dad's names are both on here.

01:47.572 --> 01:50.306
Bummer. I'm not half dragon.

01:50.342 --> 01:52.142
Hang on.

01:52.177 --> 01:54.244
If I was born just before midnight,

01:54.279 --> 01:55.478
and you were born just after,

01:55.514 --> 01:58.214
that means we were
born on separate days.

01:58.250 --> 02:01.050
Wait, you guys have different birthdays?

02:01.086 --> 02:03.419
Mom and Dad never told us. So they lied?

02:03.455 --> 02:06.356
What else have they been lying about?

02:06.391 --> 02:08.458
If I make this face,
will it really get stuck?

02:11.062 --> 02:12.195
No!

02:12.230 --> 02:13.429
Come on.

02:13.465 --> 02:15.431
Mom and Dad owe us an explanation.

02:15.467 --> 02:17.267
They're lucky you're not half dragon,

02:17.302 --> 02:19.202
or they'd be in for quite the crisping.

02:21.239 --> 02:23.306
Guys, no, you can't tell Mom and Dad.

02:23.341 --> 02:25.375
They'll know you were up here.

02:25.410 --> 02:28.311
They'll know I was up here.

02:28.346 --> 02:30.413
Virtual reality...

02:30.448 --> 02:32.382
so much better than real reality.

02:32.417 --> 02:34.250
